<ul style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;"><li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Propiation (substitute sacrifice) is what Jesus is described as for us. This fulfills the old law of sacrifice for us permanently.</li>
<li style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">&quot;God set forth&quot; explains that it was not just Jesus coming on His own accord to satisfy some angry and vengeful Father. The Father was the one who set everything in motion for the redemption of sinners in the first place.</li></ul></body></html>